@database sneaker.guide
@smartwrap

@node Main "Sneaker"
This is a quickie little program to help make @{"Sneaker networks" link snet}
 a little more efficient.
@endnode

@node IconM "Sneaker - Hide"
Closes the windows and opens an AppIcon on the Workench screen.
@endnode

@node SetM "Sneaker - Settings"
Used to set the project specific information.
@endnode

@node AboutM "Sneaker - About"
See @{"Main" link Main}
@endnode

@node Quit "Sneaker - Quit"
Let me out, NOW!!!
@endnode

@node Freshen "Sneaker - Freshen"
@{b}Freshen@{ub} is used to set the archive bit for all the files
that match the specified pattern that are in @{"SrcDir" link SrcDir}.
@endnode

@node Show "Sneaker - Show"
@{b}Show@{ub} is used to show a list of all the files that have
changed since the last time that the @{b}Freshen@{ub} button was
pressed.
@endnode

@node snet "Sneaker - Sneaker Network"
The cheapest kind, requiring no special computer hardware---just a good
pair of sneakers.

You copy the files onto a floppy and walk it over to the destination
computer.
@endnode
